  "time_ut": 1661506416,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d86\u0db1\u0dba\u0db1 \u0dad\u0dc4\u0db1\u0db8 \u0da2\u0db1\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d86\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dc2\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dad\u0dbb\u0dca\u0da2\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Import ban is a threat to people's security",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Pubudu Jayagoda, the education secretary of the militant socialist party, said today (26) that the government's move to ban the import of 300 types of goods has posed a serious threat to the people's livelihoods and security, and that there is a risk of losing lakhs of jobs in many fields with this import ban.",
        "Mr. Jayagoda said that by banning the import of signal systems and related spare parts for trains, there is a serious concern about train accidents and he also mentioned that the import of vehicle fire extinguishing equipment has also been restricted.",
        "Mr. Jayagoda said that due to the ban on the import of many equipment in the construction sector including iron, aluminum and water pipes, the operations of large-scale construction companies have decreased by 60 percent and due to the ban on the import of raw materials required for the production of paper and cardboard, jobs in the newspaper and book sectors have been severely threatened. .",
        "Mr. Jayagoda further mentioned that this import ban will severely damage the economy by banning the import of many farming equipments including harvesters."
      ],
